    <dcterms:title>In Harrisonburg, Va., attorneys discuss Judge John Paul's ruling on Charlottesville and Warren County, Va., public school integration</dcterms:title>
    <dcterms:description>Virginia Attorney General Albertis S. Harrison talks to reporters about Judge John Paul's decision to outlaw the use of public school teachers in private educational systems. Paul says that the state must either integrate its schools or divorce itself completely from public education. In the Harrisonburg, Va., courtroom, attorneys Oliver Hill, Samuel W. Tucker, Frank Reeves, and Robert L. Carter talk with Harrison and among each other.  A group of women leave the office of a public official.</dcterms:description>
